Pooja Vastrakar bowling to Alyssa Healy, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Alyssa Healy gashes the ball to point, and it appears to be struck with immense power. However, it goes straight into the hands of Jemi, who has been exceptional in the field today, with the ball seemingly following her. Jemi showcases her agility by getting low to attempt a dipping catch. But, before Healy departs, the TV umpire is called upon to determine if the catch was taken cleanly. Most replays are blurred due to the ball's rapid movement, prompting the TV umpire to request additional angles. This is a crucial juncture in the match, and with no soft signal given, the TV umpire's decision will be final. The verdict arrives! NOT OUT! The TV umpire states, "I don't have conclusive evidence to confirm a clean catch." Healy survives due to the lack of definitive evidence, leaving the outcome uncertain. A pivotal moment in the game with the decision hanging in the balance.
